                <fr:title text="Projection functions and surjections">Projection functions and <fr:link href="/jms-00M8/" title="Surjection" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00M8/" display-uri="jms-00M8" type="local">surjections</fr:link></fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter><html:p>The projection function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\pi _1\colon  A\times  B\to  A]]></fr:tex> sending <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (a,b\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/jms-00M8/" title="Surjection" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00M8/" display-uri="jms-00M8" type="local">surjective</fr:link> if and only if either <html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B \not =\varnothing ]]></fr:tex></html:span> or <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A=\varnothing ]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>Suppose that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\pi _1\colon  A\times  B\to  A]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/jms-00M8/" title="Surjection" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00M8/" display-uri="jms-00M8" type="local">surjective</fr:link>. We proceed by cases on whether <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is empty:</html:p>
 <html:ol><html:li>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is empty, we are done.</html:li>
  <html:li>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is inhabited by some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex>, then by assumption there exists <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u\in  A\times  B]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\pi _1{\mathopen {}\left (u\right )\mathclose {}}=a]]></fr:tex>. Thus <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> is inhabited by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\pi _2{\mathopen {}\left (u\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</html:li></html:ol>

 <html:p>Conversely, suppose that either <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B\not =\varnothing ]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A=\varnothing ]]></fr:tex>. Fixing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex>, we must show that there exists <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u\in  A\times  B]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\pi _1{\mathopen {}\left (u\right )\mathclose {}}=a]]></fr:tex>. If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A=\varnothing ]]></fr:tex>, then we have a contradiction already; on the other hand, if there exists any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b\in  B]]></fr:tex>, we may define <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u:={\mathopen {}\left (a,b\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> and we are done.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
